- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) - The paper uses publication output as one of the control variables, which is a common topic in digital libraries research. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper does not directly discuss software engineering, but it does use panel data analysis, which is a common method in software engineering research. 
- cs.PH (Physics and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of democracy on scientific influence, which can be seen as a topic in the intersection of physics and society. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper uses international research collaboration as one of the control variables, which is a common topic in information retrieval research.
